formula_28
where the symbols are defined as above. This can be compared with the formulae for the volumes of a cylinder (), a hemisphere (, where ), and a cone (). is the aperture area of the dish, the area enclosed by the rim, which is proportional to the amount of sunlight a reflector dish can intercept. The surface area of a parabolic dish can be found using the area formula for a surface of revolution which gives
